cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the performance and security of blockchains, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on consensus protocols and transaction execution suggests that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are likely sub-categories. The analysis of historical data and proposal of an analytical model suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the discussion of opportunities to speed up and secure blockchains suggests cs.SE (Software Engineering) as a potential sub-category.
